track_notes:
Parking at SH68403019. Forest tracks past Graigddu-isaf and south to SH67352870. Take Bwlch Drws-Ardudwy path. At SH66482823 turn left before wall to drop and cross 2nd wall. Steep ascent from SH66452816. Mostly easy enough to follow.

Cairn at summit with a nice wall to set up against.

Total time (including ops): 8h 5m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T3. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Rhinogydd Circuit from Cwm Nantcol. Oct 2021.

track_notes:
Start at parking area just at the public road end SH684302.  
Follow public foot path signs along forestry tracks to SH673286 where the public footpath continues WSW towards the col between Rhinog Fach and Fawr.  Ascend to the top of the col and continue down the far side approx 500m losing 50m in height.
Where the path flattens you can see a ladder stile on your left (south) crossing the wall on a rough path. SH659280. Cross the stile and ascend south, steeply at first, to reach Llyn Cwmhosan.  Continue south following rough paths to a cairn SH660270.  Fork left and head E then climb quite steeply NE up a well defined rough path to the shoulder SH664274.  
From here head south over easier ground to the summit.  Beware there are multiple paths in this area so take care not to end up following one down away from the summit.
Summit is a fine spot with large cairn.
track_title: From public road end in NW  Avoiding steep section on North ridge
